        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2296672498" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7382296277071421165">Reliquary is to Relic what Aliens is to Alien. Both are them are great books (and movies) and while the first book (movie) focuses on a single predator in a closed space, the latter focuses on multiple predators in larger space.<br/><br/>Reliquary, while being as intense as Relic, also manages to have time for character development. In addition to the gang of four we saw in Relic (Pendergast, D&apos;Agosta, Margo &amp; Bill), we have new characters who also have their own unique stories.The great writing as well a</span>
  <span id="freeText7382296277071421165" style="display:none">Reliquary is to Relic what Aliens is to Alien. Both are them are great books (and movies) and while the first book (movie) focuses on a single predator in a closed space, the latter focuses on multiple predators in larger space.<br /><br />Reliquary, while being as intense as Relic, also manages to have time for character development. In addition to the gang of four we saw in Relic (Pendergast, D'Agosta, Margo &amp; Bill), we have new characters who also have their own unique stories.The great writing as well as the fast pacing carries over from Relic. <br /><br />In conclusion, Reliquary is a great sequel to Relic.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7382296277071421165" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
